{
  "stem": "25639.5",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Although, I suppose the men had a stronger showing of that, because of the 10 men that's needed in order to create a service, a minyan. 10 men is called a minyan.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In the women-- in the Orthodox movement, women are not counted in-- in a minyan.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But I belong to a-- the Conservative movement, which is sort of like the Democratic party, in the middle of the road.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And-- And in our synagogue, a woman is counted as one of the 10.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But in Auschwitz-Birkenau, the women would find-- we would find them davening, praying, in the corner of the barrack, very, very intently, and sometimes with tears.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And-- And others prayed in their-- in their beds, in their bunk beds.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Others gave up on religion.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And there were still others who-- who cared.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Who cared, and who were confused, such as myself.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I come from an Orthodox family.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We had a strictly kosher household of the first 14 years of my life, until Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And my grandpa was a Talmud Chacham knowledgeable in the Talmud, and my granduncle as well.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And was-- taught the whole area-- the teachers in the whole area-- in his-- his time.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And I found it beautiful, and peaceful, and soothing, and strengthening.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When I went to Auschwitz, my mother remained strong throughout the whole ordeal.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I had-- there were times when I really questioned whether there was a God.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I wondered, if there was a God, how could he see all this terrible disaster to happen?",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "This calamity to come down on us?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[SOBS] And yet, this-- this feeling of neither here nor there would make me feel weaker.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It would-- I felt-- this was particularly true later, when I no longer was with my mother and sister.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
